configuring model response languages (including Simplified Chinese)\n\n3. **Enhanced Vim Operations** - Expanded Vim mode capabilities for better terminal-based development\n\n4. **Shift+Enter for Line Breaks** - Native support for multi-line input without additional configuration\n\n5. **Session Teleportation** - New `/teleport` command allows seamless transfer of work sessions between devices\n\n6. **Agent & Skill Hooks** - Support for adding hooks directly in Agent and Skill frontmatter\n\n7. **Tool Permission Wildcards** - Wildcard support for tool permissions when agents are denied access\n\n8. **MCP Dynamic Updates** - Model Context Protocol improvements\n\n9. **Async Sub-Agents** - New asynchronous capabilities for agent operations\n\n10. **Improved Tool Refusal Handling** - Agents no longer terminate when users deny specific tool usage\n\n### Improvements Summary:\n- **30+ new features**\n- **40+ bug fixes** (including security vulnerabilities, Chinese input issues, terminal compatibility)\n- **10+ performance and experience optimizations**\n\n### Notable Updates Timeline:\n- **January 7, 2026**: Claude Code 2.1.0 released\n- **January 8-9, 2026**: Quick follow-up with 2.1.1 hotfix\n- **Later iterations**: Version continued to 2.1.4+ with additional refinements\n\n### How to Upgrade:\n```bash\nnpm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n# or\nnpm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code@latest\n```\n\nThen verify with: `claude --version`\n\n---\n\n## 🔒 February 2026: Security Module\n\nOn **February 20, 2026**, Anthropic released a web-based **Claude Code Security** module that combines automated scanning with human-like analysis capabilities to identify business logic defects and access control vulnerabilities.\n\n---\n\nThis update represents Claude Code's evolution from a pure command-line tool to a mature development platform, with developers reporting up to **10x efficiency improvements** in real-world usage.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above i