andards\n   - Will be free for 3 months to help more developers experience it\n   - Maintains normal running speeds despite improved performance\n\n2. **Context Window Indicator**\n   - New visual indicator showing real-time context window usage\n   - Helps users monitor AI interaction resources and predict capacity limits\n   - Useful for deciding when to start new sessions\n\n3. **Multi-Session Parallel View**\n   - Users can now view and operate multiple Cascade sessions side-by-side\n   - Available through split panes or tabs in a single window\n\n4. **Git Worktree Support**\n   - Cascade now supports Git worktrees for complex development scenarios\n   - Resolves file conflict issues by allowing multiple sessions on different branches of the same repository\n\n5. **Cascade Hooks**\n   - Developers can set up hooks that trigger specific actions at certain points in the agent lifecycle (e.g., after each message is sent)\n   - Enhances interaction flexibility\n\nThe release significantly upgrades multi-agent workflows, performance, accessibility, and terminal reliability, further establishing Windsurf as a popular AI code editor.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
